## 9. Extension points (summary)

| Need | Where you act | Impact on engine |
|------|---------------|------------------|
| New schema format (e.g. YAML) | new SchemaParser | none |
| New storage backend | new DataSource | none |
| New report destination | new ReportSink | none |
| New rule (existing logic) | row in the catalog | none |
| New rule (brand-new logic) | type in the RuleRegistry | none |
| Reorder / add a phase | phase configuration | none |
| Enable/disable a rule | catalog `enabled` field | none |
| Exempt columns from a rule | catalog `exempted_columns` field | none |
| New data format (XML) | new DataFormat (DataSource + structural rules) | core unchanged (cf. §8) |

---

## 10. Areas to confirm / open decisions

- **Strict or partial gate in the Structure phase**: does a file with an extra column
  block everything, or do we tolerate some columns and continue on the others?
- **CROSS policy on very large volumes**: acceptable memory bound for
  duplicate/uniqueness rules (key materialization).
- **Value of N** (size of error samples in the report).
- **Remaining enumerated types** (`Currency`, `PriceMode`): exact constraints to
  confirm (ISO 3-letter length? closed list?).
